#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:1
msgid "Behringer CMD STUDIO 4a"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:4
msgid ""
"The Behringer CMD STUDIO 4a is a 2 deck controller that supports 4 virtual "
"decks and has a built in 4 channel (one stereo main, one stereo headphones) "
"USB sound card built in."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:8
msgid ""
"[Manufacturer’s product "
"page](https://www.behringer.com/en/products/0700-aac)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:9
msgid ""
"[Mixxx Forum Thread](https://mixxx.discourse.group/t/new-behringer-cmd-"
"studio-4a-mapping/15604)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:13
msgid "Mixxx Sound Hardware Preferences"
msgstr "Preferências de Hardware de Som do Mixxx"

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:16
msgid "Main output: channels 1-2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:17
msgid "Headphone output: channels 3-4"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:19
msgid "Mapping description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:22
msgid ""
"Most of the buttons and knobs on the controller behave as they are labelled:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:25
msgid "Behringer CMD STUDIO 4a Layout"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:31
msgid "Behringer CMD STUDIO 4a (top view)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:33
msgid ""
"The only major departure from the above are the 4 “FX Control” knobs and "
"buttons at the top of each deck."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:36
msgid "Mixer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:39
msgid ""
"The HIGH, MID, and LOW EQ knobs & kill buttons, deck faders, cross-fader, "
"main, and headphone monitoring (mix & volume) knobs all operate as labelled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:42
msgid "Each deck also has a gain knob (leftmost “FX Control” knob)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:44
msgid "Navigation Control"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:47
msgid "The BROWSE knob scrolls thorough the track list in the library panel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:48
msgid ""
"The BROWSE LEFT/RIGHT buttons move through the library tree (and can also "
"select effects, see later)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:50
msgid "The ENTER button expands/collapses library tree items."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:52
msgid "Deck Select Buttons"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:55
msgid ""
"The deck select buttons (A, B, C, D) make the respective “virtual” deck "
"active."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:57
msgid "On the left deck: A = Channel 1, C = Channel 3."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:58
msgid "On the right deck: B = Channel 2, D = Channel 4."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:60
msgid "Transport Control"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:63
msgid ""
"The deck LOAD buttons will load the currently highlighted track in the "
"library window into that deck."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:65
msgid ""
"The deck CUE, PLAY, SYNC, and LOOP buttons work as labelled (SYNC toggles "
"sync lock for the deck)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:68
msgid "Wheels"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:71
msgid ""
"While a track is playing, spinning the wheels temporarily speeds up or slows"
" down the track."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:73
msgid "When a track is stopped, spinning the wheels results in a fast search."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:75
msgid ""
"When the top wheel surface is touched the wheels act as as a precision jog."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:77
msgid ""
"When the SCRATCH button is activated, moving the wheel while touching the "
"top surface scratches the track."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:80
msgid "Hot Cue Buttons"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:83
msgid ""
"If not currently set, pressing a HOT CUE button sets that hot cue at the "
"current playback position."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:85
msgid ""
"If already set, pressing a HOT CUE button jumps to that hot cue position."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:87
msgid ""
"If the DEL button is \\*held*, pressing an already set HOT CUE button will "
"clear that hot cue."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:89
msgid ""
"Tapping the DEL button toggles {ref}`DEL-mode <del-mode>`. The button will "
"light up blue. DEL-mode alters some of the other button functions like a "
"shift button on other controllers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:93
msgid "Playback Pitch/Rate"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:96
msgid "The pitch sliders control the pitch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:97
msgid ""
"The PITCH BEND +/- buttons step the playback rate up or down (pressing both "
"resets the rate back to normal)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:99
msgid ""
"The LOCK buttons turn on key lock so the pitch doesn’t change when the "
"playback rate changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:101
msgid ""
"The PITCH BEND button lights will indicate whether the current pitch is "
"higher or lower than normal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:104
msgid "FX Control Buttons"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:107
msgid "These do not control effects; they have other functions:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:109
msgid ""
"FX Control button 1 toggles the deck slip-mode on/off, (button lights blue "
"when active). Slip-mode is not available in any Mixxx skin yet so may be "
"unfamiliar. When slip-mode is active, playback continues (muted in the "
"background) during a loop/scratch etc. Once disabled, playback will resume "
"where the track would have been if the loop/scratch has not taken place "
"(thus preserving the track beat)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:115
msgid ""
"FX Control button 2 toggles the deck repeat mode, (button lights blue when "
"active)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:117
msgid "FX Control button 3 can be tapped to adjust the beat-grid position."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:118
msgid ""
"FX Control button 4 toggles the deck quantise mode on/off, (button lights "
"blue when active)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:121
msgid "FX Control knobs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:124
msgid "FX Control knob 1 = Deck gain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:125
msgid ""
"FX Control knob 2 = FX 1 “super” control (FX unit 1 on left deck, unit 3 on "
"right deck)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:127
msgid ""
"FX Control knob 3 = FX 2 “super” control (FX unit 2 on left deck, unit 4 on "
"right deck)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:129
msgid ""
"FX Control knob 4 = Deck “quick effect” control (by default this is a filter"
" effect but can be changed in Mixxx’s preferences)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:132
msgid "FX Assign Buttons"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:135
msgid ""
"Tapping either of the 2 FX ASSIGN buttons on each deck will toggle the "
"deck’s output to one (or both) of two effects in the (default) 4-unit "
"effects rack. The left deck (A or C) can be assigned to effect units 1 "
"and/or 2. The right deck (B or D) can be assigned to effect units 3 and/or "
"4."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:140
msgid ""
"\\*Holding\\* an FX ASSIGN button allows the effect in that effect unit to "
"be changed using the BROWSE LEFT/RIGHT buttons."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:144
msgid "DEL-mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:147
msgid ""
"DEL-mode is activated by *tapping* the deck’s hot cue DEL button (the button"
" will light up blue). This is equivalent to a shift button on other "
"controllers and so changes the behaviour of a number of the controller "
"buttons as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:152
msgid ""
"The HOT CUE buttons act as auto-loop triggers (when \\*held*) in DEL-mode. "
"The button layout follows the default “LateNight” skin (i.e. top row = [1/8]"
" to [1], bottom row = [2] to [16] beats). Longer auto-loops can be “locked” "
"(so the HOT CUE button doesn’t have to be held) by pressing the LOOP ON/OFF "
"button after an auto-loop is selected, (locked/playing auto-loops can also "
"be resized by selecting a different auto-loop and then re-locking the new "
"size with the LOOP ON/OFF button)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:160
msgid "The CUE button triggers reverse playback (while \\*held*)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:161
msgid ""
"The PLAY button triggers reverse-slip playback (while \\*held*). NB: if you "
"already have slip-mode activated before you trigger reverse-slip playback, "
"(e.g. by having pressed FX-Control button 1), then slip-mode will be turned "
"off as soon as you release the PLAY button (and you will return to the "
"playback point where you would have been if you hadn’t altered the "
"playback)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:167
msgid ""
"The PITCH BEND +/- buttons step the key up/down without altering the "
"playback rate. If both PITCH BEND buttons are pressed together, the playback"
" key is reset to normal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:171
msgid "Auto-Loops and Slip-Mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:174
msgid ""
"There are no “slip-mode aware” skins in Mixxx yet so the auto-loop behaviour"
" of this controller (which \\*is\\* “slip-mode aware”) may be a little "
"different than you might expect to take advantage of this feature."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:179
msgid "Auto-loop buttons are (by default) only active when held."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_studio_4a.md:180
msgid ""
"In slip-mode, releasing an auto-loop button will immediately “re-sync” "
"playback (by disabling, then immediately re-enabling slip mode), you may see"
" the slip-mode button flash briefly when this happens. This allows for some "
"very interesting “slip-auto-loop” effects."
msgstr ""
